The paper discusses the development of a cyber-physical testbed for training and research, with a focus on security. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with the integration of information and communication technologies with physical systems, which falls under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The use of SCADA technologies also suggests a possible fit with the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The development of adversarial scenarios and detection strategies suggests a possible fit with the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the architecture of the testbed, which suggests a possible fit with the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
